 the nav via a client-side Supabase subscription.\\n- Any change to the Stripe checkout API route, the webhook handler, or the billing portal route.\\n- Any change to the Free plan CTA.\\n- Mobile redesign of the nav beyond appending the two new items to the existing sheet.\\n\\n## Further Notes\\n\\n- The cadence toggle state lives in the `Pricing` client component. The `GetProButton` reads the current cadence from the same component scope; no new state container is introduced.\\n- The `notice` parameter is intentionally separate from `error` so future notices (e.g. \\\"session expired\\\") can be added without overloading error semantics or styling.\\n- Sanitization for `next` is already implemented on the login page; no duplicate sanitizer is added on the calling side. The CTA is permitted to construct any path-relative `next` and trust the login page to reject unsafe values.\",\"labels\":[],\"number\":29,\"state\":\"OPEN\",\"title\":\"Auth-gated Get Pro flow + logged-in nav state\"}","stderr":"","interrupted":false,"isImage":false,"noOutputExpected":false}}
